RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 2
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Seller provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Services ("Reactive Supply Service") from the facility located in Westville, NJ ("Eagle Point Facility") to the Pennsylvania-New Jersey-Maryland Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") in order to assist in maintaining transmission voltages within acceptable limits on the PJM transmission system. This Rate Schedule No. 2 sets forth Sellers revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Power Service to PJM, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides for PJM to pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirements for Reactive Supply Services.
Sellers monthly revenue requirement consists of the sum of the charges for the following: (1) The Fixed Capability Revenue Requirement; and (2) Heating Losses Component; adjusted for the relative proportion of the Eagle Point Facility generation sources that are Capacity Resources. Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Rate Schedule shall be effective on April 12, 2012.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
1) FIXED CAPABILITY COMPONENT
The annual revenue requirement for the Fixed Capability Component is $436,127.
2) HEATING LOSSES COMPONENT
The annual revenue requirement for the Heating Loss Component is $146,592.
3) CAPACITY RESOURCE ADJUSTMENT
The Capacity Resource Adjustment is the percentage of capacity resource capability to the total generation capacity. The percentage Capacity Resource Adjustment is 82.5%.
The total monthly revenue requirement is $40,061.9340,049 [($436,127 + $146,592)*82.5% /12] -2-
